==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anchor light
<hw>Anchor light</hw>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The lantern shown at
night by a vessel at anchor. International rules of the road require
vessels at anchor to carry from sunset to sunrise a single white light
forward if under 150 feet in length, and if longer, two such lights, one
near the stern and one forward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anchorman</ent>⟦br⟧
